In the Matter of Samuel B. BARNETT, Debtor; Samuel B. BARNETT v. STATE MUTUAL LIFE ASSURANCE CO. et al. Nos. 5569, 5621. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Jan. 30, 1936. Jacob G. Grossberg and Charles W. Mead, both of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Don Kenneth Jones and Thomas R. Mulroy, both of Chicago, Ill., for appellee State Mutual Life Assurance Company. Isaac B. Lipson and A. C. Lewis, both of Chicago, Ill., for appellee Chicago Title & Trust Company, as Conservator of the Estate of Florence Klein, Incompetent.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges, and BRIGGLE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

It is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that the order or decree of the said District Court in this cause appealed from he, and the same is hereby, affirmed with costs.
